place.name: AISTHORPE
place.gazetteerText: AISTHORPE, or East Thorpe, a parish in the district and county of Lincoln; on the Wolds, near Ermine street, 4 miles NE of Saxelby r. station, and 6½ NNW of Lincoln. Post Town, Saxelby under Lincoln. Acres, 803. Real property, £1,214. Pop., 100. Houses, 18. The property, and that of West Thorpe, are divided among four proprietors. The living is a rectory, united to the vicarage of West Thorpe, in the diocese of Lincoln Value, £289. Patron, J. Milnes, Esq. The church is tolerable. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
